This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and text analysis. Specifically, it focuses on identifying fake news using emotion cognizant representations of news articles. Therefore, it could also be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with social impact and misinformation. Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques, which could place it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper also involves information retrieval techniques, which could place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
